                            <p><strong>Purchase method: consolidation entries</strong>  </p>
                            <p>In case of purchase method (full consolidation)  the software automatically consolidates parent and subsidiary reporting on a  technical level (i.e. using basic IFRS rules), as described above. User's goal  is to make adjustment entries that account for goodwill, non-controlling  interests, remove investments from the balance sheet. Such entries are made in  correspondence with equity indicators B, C, D (see the chart above). Below are  the sample entries (may be different in each individual case, that is why user  needs to make them with due consideration):</p>
                            <table width="100%" border="1" cellpadding="4" cellspacing="0">
                                <tr>
                                    <td align="center" valign="middle"><strong>Debit</strong></td>
                                    <td align="center" valign="middle"><p align="center"><strong>Credit</strong></p></td>
